.TH "qcom_scm_call_atomic" 9 "qcom_scm_call_atomic" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qcom_scm_call_atomic \- atomic variation of qcom_scm_call()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" qcom_scm_call_atomic
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct qcom_scm_desc *desc "  ","
.BI "struct qcom_scm_res *res "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device
.IP "desc" 12
Descriptor structure containing arguments and return values
.IP "res" 12
Structure containing results from SMC/HVC call
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sends a command to the SCM and waits for the command to finish processing.
This can be called in atomic context.
